{
  "stem": "19690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 61.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The temple for us, in most cases, I would say, was always a happy experience-- although as a child, you look at it different.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It's a pain to have to sit there for six hours or four hours.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But later on, in retrospect, it was a good learning experience.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In '36, when I went into first grade, was the first year that the Germans had ruled that no Jewish kids could go into public school.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So at that time, our synagogue had a room-- a meeting room upstairs that was then converted to become a classroom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had Rabbi Marx, who became our teacher.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had all the classes in one room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was around 15 or 20 children all together in town at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were all the grades that you could imagine.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And what he would do is he would do a little bit with one class and with another class.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in our-- in my class, the first grade class, there were four of us at the time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were some classes where there was only one student.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then there would be skipping a-- a grade, maybe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there would be two or three in another grade.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he would teach at whatever grade level they were.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the teaching was mostly done around his desk because it was too difficult and too interruptive to do it throughout the room, with everybody else then having been disturbed because he would assign us other things to do.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The school was every day, Monday through Friday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Wednesday afternoons, when normally we would not have school, because the German kids had Wednesday afternoons off, we would go to school.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
